+ * instead of at every call site.
+ *
+ * GCC's -Warray-bounds can misfire here after small_vector's methods get
+ * inlined several levels deep into constructors of larger aggregates
+ * (observed for dxbc_spv::ir::Type embedding small_vector<BasicType,8>
+ * inside dxbc_spv::ir::Op): GCC's object-size tracker (built on top of
+ * __builtin_object_size-style reasoning) associates the memcpy's
+ * destination pointer with the *static* type of an unrelated outer
+ * temporary that happens to be under construction at the same source
+ * location, rather than with the actual (correctly sized) heap or
+ * embedded-union storage backing the vector. The access itself is safe:
+ * both `dst` and `src` are always live, correctly-sized buffers of at
+ * least `count` elements, as guaranteed by every caller having already
+ * called reserve()/pick_capacity() beforehand. This is a variant of the
+ * pattern tracked upstream as GCC PR 108088 / PR 106762 (false-positive
+ * -Warray-bounds through union-based small-buffer-optimized containers).
+ * Clang does not emit this warning for the equivalent code. */
